# CompassAlpha · Conformance rules (example)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These rules are the machine-checkable subset of YOUR Charter. The gate
# enforces exactly what is listed here, fail-closed — nothing more, nothing less.
# Replace every line below with rules derived from your own invariants and
# canonical-ways. Keep it short; a rules file you trust beats a long one you don't.
#
# Format:
#   forbid       <ERE regex>  :: <message shown when it matches>
#   require-cite <path-glob>          # commits touching these must cite substrate
#
# Lines starting with # are comments. One rule per line.

# --- example forbid rules (Charter "canonical ways" / invariants) ------------
forbid  parseFloat\(.*(price|amount|total|money)  :: Money is integer minor units, never a float (Charter invariant).
forbid  (SELECT|INSERT|UPDATE).*FROM.*\$\{          :: No string-interpolated SQL; use the repository layer (Charter canonical way).
forbid  FIXME                                       :: Resolve FIXMEs (or convert to a tracked ticket) before merge.

# --- example require-cite rule (provenance law) ------------------------------
# Commits that change doctrine or schema must cite the substrate they derive from.
require-cite  docs/spec/*
require-cite  *.schema.*
